        "description": "Typical range for industrial pulsed fiber lasers cleaning metals like Inconel; starting at 100 W balances efficiency and safety to avoid melting (Inconel melting point ~1300-1400°C); max safe ~300-500 W with proper scanning to prevent substrate damage. Source: IPG Photonics YLR series specs and study in Optics and Lasers in Engineering (2018) on Ni-based alloys."
